# Terminal command policy

## Shell invocation (critical — auto-run depends on this)

**Never** chain directory changes into the command string:

```text
# BAD — prefix is "cd", not allowlisted target; triggers approval
cd C:\path\to\project && npx tsc --noEmit
cd path; Get-ChildItem
Set-Location path; git status
```

**Always** set directory on the Shell tool and run a **direct** allowlisted command:

```text
# GOOD — command string starts with allowlisted prefix
working_directory: C:\Users\collo\.cursor\projects\empty-window\investor-quest
command: npx tsc --noEmit

working_directory: <repo-root>
command: Get-ChildItem src
command: Select-String -Path src\*.ts -Pattern "foo"
command: git status
command: npm run dev
```

The **first token** of `command` must match an entry in `~/.cursor/permissions.json`. Prefix matching is literal from the start of the string.

One Shell call = one command. No `&&`, `;`, or `|` unless every segment is separately allowlisted (avoid chains entirely).

## Enable auto-run (required)

User has **Auto-Run in Sandbox** enabled. `permissions.json` is ignored in **Ask Every Time** mode. Global file: `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\permissions.json` (template in `.cursor/permissions.json`).

Matching commands run immediately (no View → Run).

## Prefer tools over shell for reads

Use **Read**, **Grep**, and **Glob** for file content and codebase search. They do not require terminal approval.

## Auto-approved prefixes

**Search & read:** `rg`, `grep`, `findstr`, `dir`, `tree`, `ls`, `type`, `cat`, `where.exe`, `Get-ChildItem`, `Get-Content`, `Select-String`, `Select-Object`, `Where-Object`, `Test-Path`

**Git read-only:** `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git show`, `git branch`, `git rev-parse`, `git remote -v`, `git config --get`, `git stash list`

**Typecheck / lint / dev:** `npx tsc`, `npx tsc --noEmit`, `npm run lint`, `npm run dev`

**GitHub CLI read-only:** `gh pr view`, `gh pr list`, `gh pr checks`, `gh pr diff`, `gh issue view`, `gh run view`, `gh api`, `gh status`

Do **not** use bare `git` or `npm` (would auto-approve `git push`, `npm install`, etc.).

`cd` / `Set-Location` alone are allowlisted but **do not use them** for navigation — use `working_directory` instead so the real command auto-runs.

## Always require user approval

- `npm install`, `npm run build`, `npm run dev:fresh`
- `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`, `git reset`, `git clean`, `git checkout` (with paths)
- `rm`, `del`, `Remove-Item`, `taskkill`, `rmdir`
- `node scripts/` that writes files, kills ports, or migrates data
- Force push, hard reset, or irreversible git operations

## Dev server

Port **3003** only: Shell `command: npm run dev` with `working_directory` set to repo root (or **Ctrl+Shift+B**).
